text:
Now, to add to my 6th message, just because you're up against a juggernaut doesn't mean you can push through.
Roblox Uno is good, but UNOfficial is the better game (with pretty much everything being better). The issue is Roblox Uno has a huge player base cause of the name. (9/15)

but I'm darn sure that Reset never once expected his game to earn him any money. I'm pretty sure it was just passion that drove the project. That passion is what we have in Roblox Teletubbies 1997 today. (8/15)

That's sort of where the labor thing comes from. On top of devs being paid little (other than the top ones), they may be doing work that won't amount to anything or may encounter something they can't figure out.
Now, that doesn't mean that kids do it for the love of money, (7/15)
@TheRikeys You guys left out the predatory sex games targeted at minors issues

The issue lies in Roblox's decisions in the later years and just overall growth of the platform.
To say there isn't a soft-monopoly with bigger games would be an understatement. I say soft-monopoly cause these games (while very popular) could be dethroned with effort... (3/15)

Roblox's golden years were in the late 2000s to mid-2010s. During this era creativity thrived. Because of Roblox's "marketing" the game was essentially built by players for players. It was genius, just make a really easy-to-use platform and makers will follow. (2/15)
